sql:
SELECT * 
FROM access_logs 
WHERE user_id = (SELECT user_id FROM users WHERE email = 'john.doe@example.com');

SELECT * 
FROM evidencereports
WHERE status = 'draft';

SELECT title 
FROM fhir_resources 
WHERE deleted_at IS NULL;

SELECT name, specialty
FROM practitioners
WHERE specialty = 'Family Medicine';

external_knowledge:
- 'health records' refers to the FHIR resources;
- 'certain type of resource' corresponds to a specified value for <specific_resource_type>;
- 'professionals of a specific role' relates to users with a specified role in the users table, corresponding to <specific_user_role>.

- High-level managers refer to users with the role 'administrator' in the system;
- Active status indicates the user account is active (active = 1);
- Viewing administrative records corresponds to having 'view' access to resources categorized as 'administrative'.

sql:
SELECT fr.title, fr.description
FROM fhir_resources fr
INNER JOIN access_controls ac ON fr.resource_id = ac.resource_id;

SELECT metadata.metadata_id, users.name
FROM metadata
INNER JOIN users ON metadata.created_by = users.user_id;

SELECT p.name, p.birth_date
FROM patients p
WHERE (strftime('%Y', CURRENT_DATE) - strftime('%Y', p.birth_date)) > 50;
